What more natural than that Davos should flatter his young master by an extravagant compliment on his infant sorr aud heir? And the congratulation was not without reason. A match, against a father's will, with an unknown and almost penniless girl, was likely enough to have brought both Pamphilus aud his family to ruin. Now his son would have an acknowledged and honourable position, with the prospect of a handsorne property.
